which kingdoms and species

00:00:48.190 --> 00:00:50.125 align:middle line:84%
account for the largest
collective mass.

00:00:50.125 --> 00:00:52.810 align:middle line:90%


00:00:52.810 --> 00:00:56.380 align:middle line:84%
Land-based plants
make up a stunning 80%

00:00:56.380 --> 00:00:57.700 align:middle line:90%
of Earth's total biomass.

00:00:57.700 --> 00:01:01.720 align:middle line:90%


00:01:01.720 --> 00:01:04.180 align:middle line:84%
If this is true,
why does it seem

00:01:04.180 --> 00:01:07.570 align:middle line:84%
that humans seem to view
them as an afterthought?

00:01:07.570 --> 00:01:11.590 align:middle line:84%
Surely, such a thriving
kingdom has some intelligence.

00:01:11.590 --> 00:01:13.990 align:middle line:84%
Is it possible that
plants have something

00:01:13.990 --> 00:01:16.660 align:middle line:90%
we can absorb besides oxygen?

00:01:16.660 --> 00:01:20.400 align:middle line:84%
And could that
something be knowledge?

00:01:20.400 --> 00:01:23.760 align:middle line:84%
Knowledge that can help us
understand our own humanity

00:01:23.760 --> 00:01:24.630 align:middle line:90%
on the planet.

00:01:24.630 --> 00:01:27.180 align:middle line:84%
>> Plant intelligence
is very sophisticated,

00:01:27.180 --> 00:01:29.190 align:middle line:84%
and we're still
trying to understand.

00:01:29.190 --> 00:01:32.610 align:middle line:10%
And it's very, very different
from human intelligence.

00:01:32.610 --> 00:01:35.760 align:middle line:10%
And it's very important
not to anthropomorphize

00:01:35.760 --> 00:01:40.740 align:middle line:10%
this intelligence, that is, to
ascribe human quality onto them

00:01:40.740 --> 00:01:43.890 align:middle line:10%
and to believe that they
manifest this intelligence

00:01:43.890 --> 00:01:45.570 align:middle line:10%
in the same way we do.

00:01:45.570 --> 00:01:48.180 align:middle line:84%
Plants through photosynthesis,
which is basically

00:01:48.180 --> 00:01:52.230 align:middle line:84%
absorbing sunlight,
carbon dioxide, and water,

00:01:52.230 --> 00:01:54.120 align:middle line:84%
they create all the
chemicals, all the

00:01:54.120 --> 00:01:57.990 align:middle line:84%
sugars that they need
to live but to also

00:01:57.990 --> 00:02:03.780 align:middle line:84%
trade with other animals,
birds, insects, other plants.

00:02:03.780 --> 00:02:06.120 align:middle line:84%
And this is a very
advanced intelligence.

00:02:06.120 --> 00:02:09.339 align:middle line:84%
There's a high level of
efficiency and conservation

00:02:09.339 --> 00:02:10.139 align:middle line:90%
of energy.

00:02:10.139 --> 00:02:14.829 align:middle line:90%


00:02:14.829 --> 00:02:19.090 align:middle line:84%
>> But the intelligence of
these plants goes even further.

00:02:19.090 --> 00:02:23.020 align:middle line:84%
Not only are they equipped with
short and long-term memory,

00:02:23.020 --> 00:02:26.220 align:middle line:84%
but they can engineer
their local environment.

00:02:26.220 --> 00:02:28.830 align:middle line:90%
Trees are the best example.

00:02:28.830 --> 00:02:31.170 align:middle line:84%
As they grow larger,
they can have

00:02:31.170 --> 00:02:35.950 align:middle line:84%
a profound effect on the soil
and organisms around them.

00:02:35.950 --> 00:02:39.580 align:middle line:84%
When a forest grows to
create its own canopy,

00:02:39.580 --> 00:02:43.210 align:middle line:84%
other plants and trees can begin
growing on the existing trees'

00:02:43.210 --> 00:02:45.100 align:middle line:90%
branches.

00:02:45.100 --> 00:02:50.020 align:middle line:84%
Plants can even communicate with
other plants and even animals.

00:02:50.020 --> 00:02:51.910 align:middle line:84%
Often, this is
through the release

00:02:51.910 --> 00:02:53.875 align:middle line:90%
of pheromones or scents.

00:02:53.875 --> 00:02:58.180 align:middle line:10%
>> The plant kingdom and
queendom is amazingly

00:02:58.180 --> 00:03:01.660 align:middle line:10%
intelligent, and we certainly
know that plants have

00:03:01.660 --> 00:03:04.240 align:middle line:10%
the ability to communicate
with each other,

00:03:04.240 --> 00:03:07.690 align:middle line:10%
that they can be
protective of one another,

00:03:07.690 --> 00:03:12.100 align:middle line:10%
that they abound in all kinds
of phytochemicals that help

00:03:12.100 --> 00:03:16.070 align:middle line:10%
to protect their immunity,
such as their essential oils.

00:03:16.070 --> 00:03:18.880 align:middle line:84%
So we're still learning
about all the wisdom

00:03:18.880 --> 00:03:21.520 align:middle line:90%
that lives in the plant realm.

00:03:21.520 --> 00:03:25.570 align:middle line:10%
>> Plants exist in a state
of consciousness that humans

00:03:25.570 --> 00:03:28.060 align:middle line:10%
don't always seem
to understand fully,

00:03:28.060 --> 00:03:31.300 align:middle line:10%
and we see them as somewhat
less evolved than us.

00:03:31.300 --> 00:03:34.180 align:middle line:84%
But plants are the
heroes of this planet.

00:03:34.180 --> 00:03:40.780 align:middle line:84%
They have provided oxygen, food,
clothing, shelter, medicine,

00:03:40.780 --> 00:03:43.510 align:middle line:84%
